//! The @onda component catalog — the single source of truth the ONDA Studio
//! agent reads. REPLACES the `ondajs` manifest, and is RICHER than it: each entry
//! carries the @onda-native Zod prop schema PLUS capability metadata the engine
//! uniquely knows — per-prop semantic `role` + `themeable`, the render `fidelity`
//! / `backend` (from `fidelity.ts`), a `sceneRole` / `occlusion` classification,
//! and an `example` prop set. So the agent generates higher-fidelity comps: it
//! prefers first-class components, leaves themeable props to the theme, and feeds
//! each prop a value that matches its meaning (frames, fractions, colors…).
//!
//! GENERATED by the catalog codegen (per-component descriptors -> this file +
//! the `<Name>.schema.ts` siblings). Re-run the codegen after changing a
//! component's props; don't hand-edit the entries.

